{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nk9sQSpgMGcsUTdkHUEU4G","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: draft\n3\t---\n4\t\n5\t# Scenario: use-git-rest-for-vault-writes\n6\t\n7\tValidates that the controller reads and writes vault task files via the git-rest HTTP API end-to-end: task creation, frontmatter update, result writeback, force-push reset (real `git push --force`), and a second writeback. Covers the full Acceptance Criteria sequence from spec 018.\n8\t\n9\t## Setup\n10\t\n11\t- [ ] `vault-obsidian-openclaw` StatefulSet running in the target namespace: `kubectlquant -n dev get sts vault-obsidian-openclaw`\n12\t- [ ] `agent-task-controller` running with `USE_GIT_REST=true`: `kubectlquant -n dev get sts agent-task-controller -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].env}' | jq '.[] | select(.name==\"USE_GIT_REST\")'`\n13\t- [ ] Controller log shows git-rest in use: `kubectlquant -n dev logs agent-task-controller-0 --tail=50 | grep \"git-rest\"`\n14\t- [ ] Local clone of `bborbe/obsidian-openclaw` available at `~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw` for the force-push step\n15\t- [ ] `TEST_ID=018test01-1111-2222-3333-444444444444` (greppable test identifier)\n16\t- [ ] No existing `tasks/$TEST_ID.md` in the vault repo\n17\t\n18\t## Action\n19\t\n20\t1. [ ] **CreateTask** — publish `CreateTaskCommand`:\n21\t   ```bash\n22\t   ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw/.claude/scripts/trading-api-write.sh dev \\\n23\t     \"/api/1.0/command/agent-task-v1/create-task\" \\\n24\t     '{\"taskIdentifier\":\"'\"$TEST_ID\"'\",\"frontmatter\":{\"assignee\":\"backtest-agent\",\"status\":\"todo\",\"phase\":\"todo\"},\"body\":\"Test task for spec-018 git-rest scenario.\\n\"}'\n25\t   ```\n26\t   Wait 10 s.\n27\t\n28\t2. [ ] **UpdateFrontmatter** — transition to `in_progress`:\n29\t   ```bash\n30\t   ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw/.claude/scripts/trading-api-write.sh dev \\\n31\t     \"/api/1.0/command/agent-task-v1/update-frontmatter\" \\\n32\t     '{\"taskIdentifier\":\"'\"$TEST_ID\"'\",\"updates\":{\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"phase\":\"in_progress\"}}'\n33\t   ```\n34\t   Wait 10 s.\n35\t\n36\t3. [ ] **WriteResult #1** — agent posts initial review:\n37\t   ```bash\n38\t   ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw/.claude/scripts/trading-api-write.sh dev \\\n39\t     \"/api/1.0/command/agent-task-v1/update\" \\\n40\t     '{\"taskIdentifier\":\"'\"$TEST_ID\"'\",\"frontmatter\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"phase\":\"ai_review\"},\"content\":\"Test task for spec-018 git-rest scenario.\\n\\n## Result\\n\\nTask completed by backtest-agent.\\n\\n## Review\\n\\nInitial review content from spec-018 scenario.\\n\"}'\n41\t   ```\n42\t   Wait 10 s.\n43\t\n44\t4. [ ] **Real force-push** — rewrite history and force-push (NOT a fast-forward push). The pre-write SHA is the parent we reset to:\n45\t   ```bash\n46\t   cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw && git fetch && git reset --hard origin/master\n47\t   PRE_WRITE_SHA=$(git rev-list -n 1 HEAD~1 -- \"tasks/$TEST_ID.md\" 2>/dev/null || git rev-parse HEAD~1)\n48\t   git reset --hard \"$PRE_WRITE_SHA\"\n49\t   git push --force origin HEAD:master\n50\t   RESET_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD)\n51\t   echo \"RESET_SHA=$RESET_SHA\"\n52\t   ```\n53\t   Wait 60 s for the controller's poll cycle to observe the force-push.\n54\t\n55\t5. [ ] **WriteResult #2** — agent posts second review after the reset:\n56\t   ```bash\n57\t   ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw/.claude/scripts/trading-api-write.sh dev \\\n58\t     \"/api/1.0/command/agent-task-v1/update\" \\\n59\t     '{\"taskIdentifier\":\"'\"$TEST_ID\"'\",\"frontmatter\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"phase\":\"done\"},\"content\":\"Test task for spec-018 git-rest scenario.\\n\\n## Result\\n\\nSecond agent result after force-push reset.\\n\\n## Review\\n\\nSecond review content.\\n\"}'\n60\t   ```\n61\t   Wait 10 s.\n62\t\n63\t6. [ ] **Restart idempotency** — kill the controller pod and replay the last write:\n64\t   ```bash\n65\t   kubectlquant -n dev delete pod agent-task-controller-0\n66\t   kubectlquant -n dev wait --for=condition=Ready pod/agent-task-controller-0 --timeout=120s\n67\t   ```\n68\t   Re-send the WriteResult #2 command verbatim.\n69\t\n70\t## Expected\n71\t\n72\t- [ ] After step 1: file `tasks/$TEST_ID.md` exists in the vault — fetch via `curl -s http://$(kubectlquant -n dev get svc vault-obsidian-openclaw -o jsonpath='{.spec.clusterIP}'):9090/api/v1/files/tasks/$TEST_ID.md`. Frontmatter has `status: todo`, `assignee: backtest-agent`, `task_identifier: $TEST_ID`.\n73\t- [ ] After step 2: frontmatter shows `status: in_progress`, `phase: in_progress`. `assignee` and `task_identifier` preserved.\n74\t- [ ] After step 3: file contains a `## Review` section with text \"Initial review content from spec-018 scenario.\". Frontmatter has `status: completed`, `phase: ai_review`.\n75\t- [ ] After step 4 (force-push): controller log shows the reset was observed. The file contents include the prior `## Review` text — either in place under `## Review`, OR moved under a `## Outdated by force-push <sha>` marker. The text \"Initial review content from spec-018 scenario.\" MUST still appear somewhere in the file. (Spec marks the rename-on-force-push as a follow-up controller-logic fix; the assertion here is the weaker, non-negotiable contract: prior review content is never silently destroyed.)\n76\t- [ ] After step 5: frontmatter shows `status: completed`, `phase: done`. The new \"Second review content.\" is present. Prior review text from step 3 is still present (somewhere — see step 4 expected).\n77\t- [ ] After step 6 (restart + replay): file bytes are identical to those produced by step 5 (idempotent replay; no extra `## Review` duplication, no missing content).\n78\t- [ ] One git commit per Kafka command on the vault repo: `cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw && git log --oneline -- \"tasks/$TEST_ID.md\"` shows a sequence with one commit per Action step (the force-push commit + the controller writes).\n79\t- [ ] Metrics: `controller_gitrest_calls_total{op=\"post\"}` non-zero. `controller_kafka_consume_paused_total` is 0 (no git-rest unavailability during the test).\n80\t\n81\t## Cleanup\n82\t\n83\t- [ ] Remove the test task file:\n84\t  ```bash\n85\t  cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/OpenClaw && git pull && git rm \"tasks/$TEST_ID.md\" && git commit -m \"spec-018 scenario: cleanup\" && git push\n86\t  ```\n87\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_9e58iwdnz9j9_1","session_id":"39ee2fda-6615-4b39-af19-b21d581ad85c","uuid":"6374533a-bc08-4c47-bade-33f117110d70","timestamp":"2026-07-08T09:01:37.377Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","task_description":"Generate prompts from spec"}
